{
  "materials": "The castle is constructed primarily of quarried black basalt and iron-reinforced granite, giving it a dark, imposing silhouette against the mountain sky. The Central Keep features 'Blood-veined Marble'—a rare stone that appears to weep crimson in humid weather. The South Industrial Zone is dominated by rusted heavy iron plating, riveted steel beams, and blackened brick chimneys. The floors are mostly cobblestone in the yards and polished slate within the Keep.",
  "lighting_scheme": "The exterior walls are lit by massive oil braziers that burn with a thick, acrid smoke, creating a permanent smog layer. The South Industrial Zone glows with the dull, rhythmic orange pulse of the vents connected to the forge below. Inside the Keep's ground level, lighting is austere—magical cold-fire sconces provide dim, bluish illumination that keeps shadows long, while the North Ward relies on utilitarian torchlight.",
  "atmosphere": "The air at ground level tastes of ozone, sulfur, and cold iron. The atmosphere is one of oppressive, industrialized militarism. The ground vibrates rhythmically—a subtle, constant thrumming from the subterranean Bloodforge machinery. In the Southeast Ward, the chaotic noise of shouting drill sergeants and shoeing horses dominates, while the Central Keep emits a heavy, threatening silence broken only by the clang of armored patrols.",
